The semi-final games of the Temple Jam Basketball Tournament takes place today with Gidi Giants taking on Anambra Flames in one of the ties at the Teslim Balogun Stadium in Surulere, Lagos. The high class Gidi boys would take on the energetic Flames in what is scheduled as the last match of the day. The first game will be an all Savannah Conference charge as Gombe Bulls host Niger Potters at the same venue. The classification matches were settled on Thursday with Comets beatingÂ  Delta 65-64 to finish fifth while Delta were sixth. Also, Oluyole best Tema Youth Basketball Club Ghana 67-66 to place seventh while the Ghanaians finished in eighth place. Yesterday served as free day, while the competition will round off tomorrow with the final match and lots of entertainment. 